fields.name: PRADERA LATERAL
fields.description:
BRIEF
• The Orient Canopy is an area within The Orient ground level food court that previously was occupied by a tugboat constructed as an original
scheme of the grander ship design.
• The tugboat was underused, and asset management strategy was able to foresee valuable use by removing it and creating an area that houses
four kiosks and a central space for activities and changeable temporary installations.
• All the area has not only improved the space by creating interest while providing diversification but also by making it valuable and income
producing.

fields.name: VERTU
fields.description:
The contract for the Edinburgh Multi Kia & MG Alterations project is a JCT Design and Build Contract 2024, specifically tailored and amended by Vertu Motors. Here’s a breakdown of key contract type and legal elements:

⸻

1. Contract Type: Design and Build (D&B)
	•	Form: JCT Design and Build Contract 2024.
	•	Employer’s Requirements and Contractor’s Proposals: The Employer has set out a detailed brief (Employer’s Requirements), and the Contractor is to respond with their own Proposals which, once accepted, form part of the Contract Documents.
	•	Design Liability: The Contractor carries full design liability for the elements within their scope, including coordination with employer’s direct contractors and integration of M&E.

⸻

2. Key Legal Provisions and Conditions
	•	Liquidated Damages: £5,000 per calendar week or pro rata.
	•	Retention: 5%.
	•	Defects Liability (Rectification) Period: 12 months from Practical Completion.
	•	Limit of Contractor’s Liability for Loss of Use: Limited to the Contract Sum.
	•	Professional Indemnity Insurance: £5,000,000 including coverage for asbestos, contamination, and mould claims, with a 12-year requirement under CDP liability.

⸻

3. Dispute Resolution
	•	Arbitration Excluded: Article 9 and Clause 9.5 are disapplied; likely disputes would go to adjudication or litigation.
	•	Adjudicator: Default nominating body is the RICS (President or Vice-President).

⸻

4. Other Legal Aspects
	•	Contract Execution: Under seal, making it a deed and thus subject to a 12-year limitation period for latent defects.
	•	Collateral Warranties: Required for all subcontractors with design responsibility. Forms and insurance levels are specified.
	•	No Third Party Rights or Framework Agreement: The contract does not include rights for tenants, purchasers, or funders unless specified later.
	•	Performance Bond: Required.
	•	Insurance Option: JCT Schedule 3 Option C applies (Employer to insure the works).

⸻

5. Health, Safety, and Legal Compliance
	•	CDM Regulations: McLaren Murdoch & Hamilton are named as Principal Designer (CDM).
	•	Building Regulations Compliance: Also coordinated through the same Principal Designer.
	•	Statutory and Planning Consents: The Contractor must obtain all required consents and approvals at their own cost (unless otherwise noted).
	•	Environmental and Legal Obligations: Explicit exclusion of deleterious materials; compliance with British Standards and Codes of Practice mandated.

fields.name: DECATHALON, LEEDS
fields.description:
Contractor award in June 2025 in advance of works starting in September 2025. 
The works comprise the refurbishment of the Front of House and external elevations of the existing Decathlon Leeds store. The total Gross Internal Area (GIA) of the store is 35,000 square feet, of which approximately 28,000 square feet forms the Front of House area. All works to the store will need to be completed outside of trading hours (Monday- Saturday: 9am-8pm, Sunday: 11am-5pm), as the store will remain live throughout the duration of the works.
